webResources.textAttributionSnippet: (en) Interior of the Church of Gärdserum. The new church was consecrated in 1857 and replaced an older church building of travel timber. From the medieval church some valuable furnishings have been preserved. The first mentioned is the triumchrycifix seen in the picture of the choir’s windows in the middle - https://www.europeana.eu/item/73/S_OM_photo_OMFB000584. AB Flygtrafik. Östergötlands museum - http://digitaltmuseum.se/021016419898. Public Domain Mark - http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/mark/1.0/
